  "prompt": "What people from other countries think about Indian Caste system?",
  "response": "Views on the Indian caste system from people in other countries vary, but generally include:\n\n1. Western Perspectives:\n- Often viewed as a discriminatory and oppressive social structure\n- Seen as a form of systemic inequality\n- Criticized for human rights violations\n- Considered a complex and deeply rooted social problem\n\n2. Academic Perspectives:\n- Studied as a unique sociological phenomenon\n- Analyzed as a historical social stratification system\n- Recognized for its historical complexity and persistent impact\n\n3. Human Rights Organizations:\n- Strongly condemn caste-based discrimination\n- Advocate for legal and social reforms\n- Consider it a violation of fundamental human rights\n\n4. Global South Countries:\n- Some have similar hierarchical social structures\n- Understand cultural nuances more contextually\n- Less likely to view it as purely negative\n\n5. UN and International Bodies:\n- Recognize caste discrimination as a form of systematic inequality\n- Push for legal protections and social interventions\n- Include caste-based discrimination in broader discussions of social justice\n\n6. Common Perceptions:\n- Often misunderstood as a purely religious phenomenon\n- Viewed as an outdated social system\n- Associated with economic and social barriers\n\nThese perspectives reflect a mix of criticism, academic interest, and ongoing discussions about social transformation.",
